1.title: What's Weirder Than Mustaches & Mushrooms?
1.plot: Nick Watt embraces the strange land of Albania while searching for a George W. Bush statue, downing 160-proof plum liquor, and meeting up with a "sworn virgin" and a hip-hop prime minister before pretending to be an American on a late-night TV show.

2.title: Le Marche & Slab City: Who Is the White Rabbit?
2.plot: Nick heads to Italy to see if cheap villas, good wine and naps are better than rent-free California RVs. He tries not to ruffle feathers with his caffeine intake and hops aboard the "Cosmic Train" to find the White Rabbit in Slab City.

3.title: Mt. Shasta: Are You There Harlan? It's Me, Nick
3.plot: Nick gets spiritual while searching for the city of Telos, looks for spaceships in a campfire, and enjoys a schvitz with Native Americans. Will UFOs, lost civilizations and New Age swag make Nick fall under the spell of California's Mount Shasta?

4.title: Venice: Will Skinny Dipping Send Me to Jail?
4.plot: Steering clear of the gondolas and tourist traps, Nick explores an abandoned island, befriends an aristocrat with a playboy boat, and winds up spending time in jail. Can Nick go off the beaten path in Venice, Italy?

5.title: Dominica: Should I Jump Into a Boiling Lake?
5.plot: Nick paints his face and snacks on eggs in the forest, takes shots of bush rum and discovers where the Rastas grow their weed in his quest to find out if Dominica is the perfect Caribbean island.

6.title: Portland: Am I White & Cuddly Enough?
6.plot: Why do locals want to "keep Portland weird"? Nick befriends a stripper with a heart of gold, joins the circus and paints the town red with an eccentric rock star to find out why so many are moving to Oregon's Rose City.

7.title: France: Are the French Really That Rude?
7.plot: Nick travels to France, where goes undercover with the Paris pee-pee police to chase "wild urine." Also: He discovers a very "un-French" sport in Marseilles; and tries to annoy the staff at a Cannes hotel.

8.title: Alaska: What Will Get Frostbitten First?
8.plot: Nick explores whether he has what it takes to survive in the farthest reaches of Alaska during a trip that takes him from Anchorage to Barrow, during which he visits oil towns and tries to stomach whale blubber.

9.title: New York: Basketball or Potatoes?
9.plot: What does gobs of money mean to two completely different New York 'hoods? Nick ventures into Harlem to play ball and out to the Hamptons to discover what potato farmers and clam diggers think of the mega-rich moving in.

10.title: Cuba: What Can I Get Away With?
10.plot: Is the Cuba we love about to disappear? As the United States normalizes relations, Nick discovers a fledgling free market in the streets of communist Havana: real estate agents, mattress repairmen and all-male go-go dancers.

11.title: OK/CO/HI: Do Cowboys Get High & Wear Hats?
11.plot: Honestly, are the leather chaps really necessary? Busting bandits in Osage, avoiding a contact high in Denver, and hanging ten in Oahu, Nick is on a quest to find out if everything he thought he knew about America is wrong.

13.title: LA: Can a Scottish Farm Boy Make It in Fakeland?
13.plot: Nick sets out on a mission to prove that his new hometown of L.A. isn't all fake smiles and bad traffic in the Season 1 finale, during which he reinvents himself as a masked wrestler, forages for fine dining and spends time with a gang of street artists.

imdb.plot outline: Follow journalist Nick Watt as he explores the world to answer burning questions such as: Are the French really rude? Do cowboys still exist? Is Albania that weird? Using his quick wit, he'll offer a point of view that is both surprising and entertaining.
